/i
:besttwo
Burns: Best two out of three?

Ohms: Rules are rules. You must submit to
our will, or face the penalty. (producing
a notebooks and a pen) First, I command
you to write the details of all major
Protest Party operations in this notebook.

Burns: Forget it.

Octinar: No, do it -

(He is cut off as spheres of energy
envelop him and Burns. The fields shrink
to marbles, and the two are trapped in
tiny prison spheres.)
/i
Ohms: And this, sir and madam, is what
happens when you fail to fulfill the
obligations of a Duel.

First marble: I don't suppose you could
let us out of these things?

Ohms: That is quite impossible.

Second marble: Botheration. I have a
crick in my neck.

- At least the property tax is low. -
/i
